# fd/rg search ignore rules
#
# Use this as a local .ignore file to exclude search noise. The include rules
# keep selected paths searchable when Git's global excludes file is also in
# effect. Project .gitignore rules may still apply unless disabled explicitly.
#
# Example:
#   ln -s ~/dotfiles/dotignore/searchignore .ignore

# Include useful paths excluded by the global Git ignore file.
!.src/
!.src/*
!.plans/
!.plans/**
!.handoff/
!.handoff/**
!draft*
!draft*/**
!.envrc
!.ignore

# Keep dependency repositories searchable, but skip their deeply nested files.
.src/*/*

